qas.question: How many volumes does the Nanjing Library have?
What is the name of the fifth largest library in China?
Which university library is larger than Nanjing University Library?

context: Nanjing Library, founded in <a0_0>1907<a0_0/>, houses <a2_0>more than 10 million volumes<a2_0/> of printed materials and is <a1_0>the third largest library in China<a1_0/>, after the National Library in Beijing and Shanghai Library. Other libraries, such as city-owned Jinling Library and various district libraries, also provide considerable amount of information to citizens. <a3_0>Nanjing University Library<a3_0/> is the second largest university libraries in China after <a4_0>Peking University Library<a4_0/>, and the fifth largest nationwide, especially in the number of precious collections.
